From: Robin Watts <Robin.Watts@artifex.com>
Date: Mon, 5 Feb 2024 11:38:44 +0000
Subject: Bug 707538: Avoid stack buffer overrun.

In stroke_add_compat() we define ourselves a temporary buffer to
hold points before we 'assign' them properly into the path.
Currently this is set to be 5 points long.

As part of the processing we call line_join_points() to add points
to this. This can add up to 5 points.

Unfortunately, we can call this with 1 point already in the buffer,
meaning that we then overflow by 1 entry.

When we return, we drop the last point - but the overflow has
already happened and the damage has been done.

The fix is simply to extend the temporary buffer by 1 entry.

Credit to Chris for spotting the issue and suggesting the fix.
---
 base/gxstroke.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/base/gxstroke.c b/base/gxstroke.c
index 23f899c6a..02a89fdc0 100644
--- a/base/gxstroke.c
+++ b/base/gxstroke.c
@@ -1,4 +1,4 @@
-/* Copyright (C) 2001-2023 Artifex Software, Inc.
+/* Copyright (C) 2001-2024 Artifex Software, Inc.
    All Rights Reserved.
 
    This software is provided AS-IS with no warranty, either express or
@@ -2274,7 +2274,7 @@ stroke_add_compat(gx_path * ppath, gx_path *rpath, bool ensure_closed,
        and another one for line join or for the ending cap.
        Note CPSI creates negative contours. */
     const gx_line_params *pgs_lp = gs_currentlineparams_inline(pgs);
-    gs_fixed_point points[5];
+    gs_fixed_point points[6];
     int npoints;
     bool const moveto_first = true; /* Keeping this code closer to "stroke_add". */
     int code;
